**Step 3: Swap characters**
```javascript
function reverseString(s) {
  let left = 0;
  let right = s.length - 1;

  while (left < right) {
    // Swap using destructuring
    [s[left], s[right]] = [s[right], s[left]];
  }
}
```
This matches pseudocode Step 3: "Swap characters"

**Step 4 & 5: Move pointers**
```javascript
function reverseString(s) {
  let left = 0;
  let right = s.length - 1;

  while (left < right) {
    [s[left], s[right]] = [s[right], s[left]];
    left++;
    right--;
  }
}
```
This matches pseudocode Steps 4 & 5: "Move pointers"

**Final Code:**
```javascript
function reverseString(s) {
  let left = 0;
  let right = s.length - 1;

  while (left < right) {
    [s[left], s[right]] = [s[right], s[left]];
    left++;
    right--;
  }
}
```

**Alternative using temp variable:**
```javascript
function reverseString(s) {
  let left = 0;
  let right = s.length - 1;

  while (left < right) {
    const temp = s[left];
    s[left] = s[right];
    s[right] = temp;
    left++;
    right--;
  }
}
```

